Description: A file name or full path referencing a data file produced by the related process that MAY be packaged with, or is accessible via, the ISA reference implementation content.
A pointer referencing a location inside the data file. This SHOULD always be specified when the data of interest is not the complete file, but a specific part of it.
A file name, full path or identifier referencing the tool with which this data object was generated.
An ontology annotation qualifying what the data describes.
The unit qualifying the value stored in the data object.
Specifies the format in which the value in the data object will be stored.
